Package org.firstinspires.ftc.robotcore.internal.usb.exception

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    RobotUsbDeviceClosedException
    RobotUsbDeviceClosedException is thrown when the robot USB layer detects that deeper layers have closed the underlying USB device.
    RobotUsbException
    RobotUsbException is the root of various kinds of exceptions thrown from the USB communications system.
    RobotUsbFTDIException
    RobotUsbFTDIException is thrown when a runtime exception is detected in the lower level USB layer.
    RobotUsbProtocolException
    RobotUsbProtocolException is thrown when a violation of the semantic protocol between RC and controller is detected.
    RobotUsbStuckUsbWriteException
    RobotUsbStuckUsbWriteException is thrown when the USB layer close the low-level FT_Device in attempt to recover from a greater system calamity but still is of the opinion that reopening the device is worthy of attempting in order to try to get the system back to normal.
    RobotUsbTimeoutException
    RobotUsbTimeoutException is thrown by the USB layer in the event that communications over the USB layer unexpectedly timeout.
    RobotUsbTooManySequentialErrorsException
    RobotUsbTooManySequentialErrorsException is thrown when too many many sequential protocol errors have occurred on the USB link for further communications to be reasonable.
    RobotUsbUnspecifiedException
    RobotUsbUnspecifiedException is thrown when an error occurs in the USB subsystem but no other more-specific exception is appropriate.
    RobotUsbWriteLockException
    RobotUsbWriteLockException is thrown when USB communications cannot proceed due to the inability to acquire the global USB write lock.
